 news have taken root. The mainstream press and political establishment dismissed anti-Obama mythology for years, registering concern only when it became difficult to deny how much power those who circulated it could command. Trash Talk demonstrates that the ascendancy of Barack Obama was never a signal of a postracial America.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aFake newszUnited States. 0aRacism against Black peoplezUnited StatesxHistoryy21st century. 0aRacismxPolitical aspectszUnited StatesxHistoryy21st century. 0aRumor in mass media. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Race & Ethnic Relations.2bisacsh  aamerica.  aamerican.  abarack obama.  acampaign.  aconspiracy.  aculture.  aelection.  aelectoral.  afake news.  afalse.  ahoax.  alies.  amedia.  anarrative.  apolisci.  apolitical science.  apolitics.  apresident.  arace.  aracism.  arumors.  asocial media.  atwenty first century.  aunited states.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022 Englishz978311099455108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022z9783110994520oZDB-23-DSL40uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520389250?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520389250423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520389250/original  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099455-1  EBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022 Englishb2022  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-DSLb2022  aZDB-23-UCY